\begin_layout Standard
The simplest continuous algorithm for exploring space is Brownian motion
 with the ODE 
\begin_inset Formula $dx_{t}=dW_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 To turn this into a sampling algorithm, for a convex function 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

