\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dx_{t}=-\nabla f(x_{t})+\sqrt{2}dW_{t}
\]

\end_inset

which can be used to sample according to the density proportional to 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{-f}$
\end_inset

.
 In this chapter we will begin with an even simpler method, which does not
 need access to the gradient or assume differentiability, only an oracle
 that can evaluate 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

.
