\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
From a warm start, the ball walk in a convex body of diameter 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 containing a unit ball has a mixing rate of 
\begin_inset Formula $O(n^{2}D^{2})$
\end_inset

 steps.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is based on two ideas: (1) most points of a convex body containing
