\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 is infinitesimally small; and then we can assume that the surface of 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is locally a hyperplane and compute the measure of 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{L}$
\end_inset

 explicitly.
 
\end_layout

