\begin_inset Formula $[\frac{1}{C},C]$
\end_inset

.
 An affine transformation is said to be an 
\emph on
isotropic tranformation
\emph default
 if the resulting distribution is isotropic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any distribution with bounded second moments has an isotropic transformation.
 It is clear that satisfying the first condition is merely a translation,
 so assume the mean is zero.
 For the second, suppose the covariance matrix is 
\begin_inset Formula $\E_{Q}(xx^{T})=A$
\end_inset

